INGREDIENTS:
- 1 pound tilapia fillets
- Salt and pepper to taste
- 4 tablespoons vegetable oil, divided
- 1 small onion, minced (about 2/3 cup)
- 3 cloves garlic, minced or pressed through garlic press (about 1 tablespoon)
- One 14.5 ounce can diced tomatoes, drained with liquid reserved
- Juice of one lemon (optional)
- Chopped fresh cilantro for garnish

INSTRUCTIONS:

Step #1: Season the fish.
Place your tilapia fillets on a plate and season them generously with salt and pepper.

Step #2: Cook the fish.
In a large skillet over medium heat, add two tablespoons of vegetable oil. Once hot, add in the seasoned tilapia fillets. Cook until golden brown on each side – about three minutes per side depending on thickness – then remove from pan and set aside.
